article_text:
Double Take 'Toons: Diagnostic Errors?

More than 2 million Americans had signed up for health insurance under the Affordable Care Act as of Jan. 1, according to the Obama administration. John Darkow gives Obamacare a barely passing grade, while Nick Anderson thinks Republicans don't view even limited success as good news.
